      About this item

      • No Blue Light Hazard & Flicker-Free Lighting: Certified to meet the IEC/TR 62778 and IEC/EN 62471 standards, Quntis monitor light bar effectively eliminates harmful blue light that may affect vision, reducing eye irritation and providing optimal eye protection. Enjoy our flicker-free illumination that provides a stable light source without worrying about eye discomfort. Experience a truly comfortable and eye-friendly illumination with Quntis computer monitor light.
      • No Screen Glare & Space Saving: The innovative asymmetrical optical design only illuminates your desk area, enhancing immersion and focus while ensuring no reflected glare on your screen. Our scientifically designed weighted clip easily mounts on top of the monitor, saving valuable desk space.
      • Auto-Dimming & Stepless Dimming: The built-in ambient light sensor continuously monitors the surrounding brightness and intelligently adjusts the existing light to 900 lux, preventing visual fatigue by avoiding excessive or insufficient lighting. The ScreenLinear monitor lamp also allows manual adjustments for both brightness and color temperature (3000K-6500K), so you can customize the lighting to your preference for optimal comfort.
      • Close to Natural Light & Ultra-High Ra98 Color Rendering Index: Our computer light bar features 78 high-quality LED beads, offering uniform and adequate lighting while minimizing shadows and glare, creating a comfortable lighting environment for reading, working, and gaming. High CRI enhances vibrant and true-to-life colors, making objects on your screen appear vivid and realistic. Perfect for professionals engaged in color work, ensuring color accuracy and minimizing eye fatigue.
      • Masterful Illumination, Empowering Eye Care: Quntis monitor reading lamp surpasses normal desk lamps by providing exceptional, eye-friendly illumination. It helps develop healthier visual habits during screen time and reduces the risk of myopia. Ideal for students, designers, and office workers, the ScreenLinear is a great solution for a comfortable visual experience, whether youre reading, gaming, or spending long hours in front of a screen.

      5 out of 5 stars
      Lights up your gaming/work setup!
      A light bar, particularly a monitor light bar for a workspace, has completely transformed my desk setup and reduced eye strain in a way I didn't expect. Its asymmetrical design is its killer feature; mounted atop my computer monitor, it focuses bright, glare-free light down onto my keyboard and documents, but never onto the screen itself. This eliminates the frustrating glare and reflections I used to get from traditional desk lamps, which is crucial for long hours in front of a display. It's essentially a dedicated task light that saves significant desk real estate, providing a clean, organized, and perfectly illuminated work zone while simultaneously enhancing the contrast and comfort of my screen viewing. Beyond just the work benefits, a versatile LED light bar offers fantastic opportunities for accent and functional lighting throughout my home. I've used smaller, strip-style bars to add sleek, modern under-cabinet lighting in the kitchen, instantly brightening the counter space for cooking and giving the whole area a high-end look. They are also brilliant for adding indirect bias lighting behind a TV or monitor, which helps to reduce the harsh contrast between a bright screen and a dark room, making late-night viewing much more comfortable. Whether for focused work or creating a better ambiance, the light bar is a simple, effective upgrade for any modern space.

      • Phil M.
        5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent monitor light at a great value!
        Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2023
        Style: ScreenLinear Pro GrayVerified Purchase
        I'd been considering a monitor desk light for some time now, but I could not justify the price tag giong as high as $200 on the BenQ "original" that sorta started it off with these types of lights. This was a couple years ago now and clearly today there are many different versions of similar monitor lights on the market, the Quntis being among them, and which appears to be a fairly close copy of the BenQ light.

        I found this one on Amazon, priced around $40 for the non-remote (remote being rather superfluous in my opinion) version and did a little comparison research to see if this might be a good fit. There are many similar monitor lights out there, some cheaper and going as low as ~$25 and some obviously more expensive. I figured the Quntis was a good middle ground price-wise and took a shot to see if this would fit the bill. Indeed it does!

        Whether or not, or how close a copy to the BenQ the Quntis is I don't know for sure, as I've never seen the alternatives, but I can say this one is very well designed and well constructed, some plastic and also some metal in the construction and on close inspection the quality is definitely there. The mounting system is simple and functional and adapted perfectly to my HP Omen gaming monitor, which I would say has a somewhat non-standard profile shape and thickness, at least at the top where the light mounts. No problem, the mount is easily adjustable and rests perfectly and securely on my top monitor edge with full confidence that it's not going anywhere, or is any way unstable or wonky.

        The light controls on top of the light are easily accessible, operated by touch and the tactile "buttons" are shaped so they can be easily felt when operating the light. There are stepless controls for brightness and color temperature, as well as a sort of "auto" button that adjusts the brightness based on the ambient light in the room, which is nice. The lightbar throws a very nice pool of light on your keyboard and desk space in front of, and not directly ON, your monitor - right where you need it - without any glare, or being too harsh. Again, the quality, brightness and temperature of the light is easily adjustable to your liking.

        The monitor mounting system is sensible, simple, highly adjustable and highly functional. Lamp is powered by USB and in my case plugs right into a USB port on my monitor and totally invisible, hidden behind. Anyway, I guess I might have got a little carried away with this review, but tldr; the Quntis is an excellent monitor light and if this is something you've been looking at, I don't think you can go wrong with this one.

      About this Item

      • No Blue Light Hazard & Flicker-Free Lighting: Certified to meet the IEC/TR 62778 and IEC/EN 62471 standards, Quntis monitor light bar effectively eliminates harmful blue light that may affect vision, reducing eye irritation and providing optimal eye protection. Enjoy our flicker-free illumination that provides a stable light source without worrying about eye discomfort. Experience a truly comfortable and eye-friendly illumination with Quntis computer monitor light.
      • No Screen Glare & Space Saving: The innovative asymmetrical optical design only illuminates your desk area, enhancing immersion and focus while ensuring no reflected glare on your screen. Our scientifically designed weighted clip easily mounts on top of the monitor, saving valuable desk space.
      • Auto-Dimming & Stepless Dimming: The built-in ambient light sensor continuously monitors the surrounding brightness and intelligently adjusts the existing light to 900 lux, preventing visual fatigue by avoiding excessive or insufficient lighting. The ScreenLinear monitor lamp also allows manual adjustments for both brightness and color temperature (3000K-6500K), so you can customize the lighting to your preference for optimal comfort.
      • Close to Natural Light & Ultra-High Ra98 Color Rendering Index: Our computer light bar features 78 high-quality LED beads, offering uniform and adequate lighting while minimizing shadows and glare, creating a comfortable lighting environment for reading, working, and gaming. High CRI enhances vibrant and true-to-life colors, making objects on your screen appear vivid and realistic. Perfect for professionals engaged in color work, ensuring color accuracy and minimizing eye fatigue.
      • Masterful Illumination, Empowering Eye Care: Quntis monitor reading lamp surpasses normal desk lamps by providing exceptional, eye-friendly illumination. It helps develop healthier visual habits during screen time and reduces the risk of myopia. Ideal for students, designers, and office workers, the ScreenLinear is a great solution for a comfortable visual experience, whether youre reading, gaming, or spending long hours in front of a screen.
